-- Verbund appoints Merrill Lynch's Kollmann as CFO
-- 
-- Tue Mar 5, 2013 12:25pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/05/us-verbund-cfo-kollmann-idUSBRE9240UZ20130305

 

 VIENNA  (Reuters) - Austrian hydropower provider Verbund ( VERB.VI ) named Peter Kollmann of Bank of America's ( BAC.N ) Merrill Lynch as its new finance chief on Tuesday. 
 Kollmann, 50, is vice chairman of corporate and investment banking for EMEA for Merrill based in Frankfurt. Three existing board members including Chief Executive Wolfgang Anzengruber had their terms extended until the end of 2018. Currently, Anzengruber is both CEO and finance chief of Verbund. (Reporting by  Georgina Prodhan )